    "id": "1ldr3iopu",
    "questionNumber": 31,
    "questionText": "<p>What is the correct order of acidity of the protons marked $$\\mathrm{A}-\\mathrm{D}$$ in the given compounds ?</p>\n",
    "options": [
      "$$\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{D}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{C}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{B}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{A}}$$",
      "$$\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{C}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{A}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{D}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{B}}$$",
      "$$\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{C}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{D}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{B}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{A}}$$",
      "$$\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{C}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{D}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{A}}>\\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{B}}$$"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "topic": "method-of-preparation-for-aldehydes",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>Acidity of an acid depends upon the stability of it's\nconjugate base.</p>\n<p>H<sub>C</sub> > H<sub>D</sub> > H<sub>A</sub> > H<sub>B</sub></p>\n<p>H<sub>C</sub> is hydrogen of carboxylic acid.</p>\n<p>H<sub>D</sub> removal will lead to stable carbanion.</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
